    <div id="content">
     <p>
      <h4 style="color: #000">
       Welcome to the Polar Meteorology Group (PMG), home of the
       <a href="http://polarmet.osu.edu/PWRF">
        Polar WRF Model (PWRF)
       </a>
       , at Byrd Polar and Climate Research Center, The Ohio State University
      </h4>
     </p>
     <p style="color: #000000; font-weight: bold; font-size: 12pt;">
      Please support our research:
      <a href="https://www.giveto.osu.edu/makeagift/OnlineGivingDonation.aspx?fund=313884">
       Polar Meteorology Group Development Fund (313884)
      </a>
     </p>
     <p style="color: #ff0000; font-weight: bold; font-size: 14pt;">
      News:
     </p>
     <p class="headline">
      <a href="/YOPP-SH">
       Year of Polar Prediction (YOPP) - Southern Hemisphere
      </a>
      <font color="#ff0000">
       (2019/01/18)
      </font>
     </p>
     <p class="headline">
      <a href="/class/geog5942_2019/ant_forecast.php">
       GEOG 5942 Antarctic Weather Forecasting Project: 2019/01/07-2019/01/18
      </a>
     </p>
     <p class="headline">
      <a href="/ASR/index.html">
       The Arctic System Reanalysis (ASR) home page
      </a>
      <font color="#ff0000">
       (2018/12/13)
      </font>
      <font color="#000000">
      </font>
     </p>
     <p class="headline">
      <a href="/AWARE">
       ARM West Antarctic Radiation Experiment (AWARE)
      </a>
     </p>
     <p class="headline">
      <a href="http://polarmet.osu.edu/Byrd_recon/">
       Warming in West Antarctica
      </a>
      <font color="#ff0000">
       (2018/09/11)
      </font>
     </p>
     <p class="headline">
      <a href="http://journals.ametsoc.org/page/connectingthetropics">
       J. Climate Special Collection, 2015-2018: Connecting the Tropics to the Polar Regions
      </a>
     </p>
     <p style="text-align: center; margin: 40px 0;">
      <img align="top" alt="collage.gif" height="386" src="/pics/collage.gif" width="532"/>
     </p>
     <p align="center">
      <a href="http://bpcrc.osu.edu/" target="_blank">
       <img align="absbottom" border="0" height="96" src="/pics/bpcrc_flag.png" style="margin-right: 1.0em;" width="156"/>
      </a>
      <a href="http://polarmet.osu.edu/" target="_blank">
       <img align="absbottom" border="0" height="96" src="/pics/pmg.png" style="margin-right: 1.0em;" width="230"/>
      </a>
      <a href="http://www.osu.edu" target="_blank">
       <img align="absbottom" border="0" height="96" src="../pics/OSU_Stacked_RedBlack.png" width="128"/>
      </a>
     </p>
     <br/>
     <p>
      <b>
       If you are in the Greater Columbus area and would like an expert from our group to speak about global climate change at your event, contact
       <a href="mailto:bromwich.1@osu.edu">
        Dr. David Bromwich
       </a>
      </b>
     </p>
     <hr>
      <p style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold;">
       <a href="/PMG_publications/nicolas_vogemann_ncomms_2017.pdf">
        Huge Melting of Ross Ice Shelf, Antarctica in January, 2016
       </a>
       (
       <a href="https://news.osu.edu/news/2017/06/15/slushpuddle/">
        News1
       </a>
       ,
       <a href="https://scripps.ucsd.edu/news/scientists-report-large-scale-surface-melting-event-antarctica-during-2015-16-el-nino">
